STATUS.md is a task tracker for a stenography system (likely Plover-adjacent, given `.utf` and `.entries` references). It prioritizes work on build automation, template bugs, and type-system standardization for dictionary generation and protocol handling across different space-constrained encodings.

The file is a markdown table sorted by impact descending, then difficulty ascending within each band. Six items: three high-impact (build docs, vim snippet tabstop bug, Array<> typing in %t context), two medium (bracket notation syntax, C++ dict %T integration), one low (dict selection menu). Impact and difficulty are stated in words, not numeric scores; the ordering itself is the priority signal.

The vim bug ("'snippet has multiple 0 tabstops' for .entries") is marked high-impact, easy-fix and should be addressed first. The Array<> typing task is high-impact but requires deciding on standardization across multiple protocols before implementation. The build process docs (high-impact, low-difficulty) should probably ship soon despite being listed first — check with stakeholders whether the table order is truly actionable or just roughly grouped.